                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14548388" author="busbey" created="Mon, 18 May 2015 17:44:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;also need 1.1 docs now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14548509" author="busbey" created="Mon, 18 May 2015 18:58:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Great point on workaround from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ndimiduk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ndimiduk&quot;&gt;Nick Dimiduk&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nick Dimiduk via hbase.apache.org 1:34 PM (22 minutes ago) to hbase-user &lt;br/&gt;
You don&apos;t need to build from the src tgz, the bin tgz contains a &quot;docs&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
directory, wherein you&apos;ll find both public-facing (@Public annotated&lt;br/&gt;
classes) and full javadocs in &quot;apidocs&quot; and &quot;devapidocs&quot; respectively. The&lt;br/&gt;
whole site and book are there too, but our release policy is to copy site&lt;br/&gt;
and book from master. The javadocs are generated with this build of this&lt;br/&gt;
release though.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14648183" author="busbey" created="Thu, 30 Jul 2015 19:42:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What do folks think about just publishing the most recent patch release in a given minor line, i.e. 1.1.1 for the 1.1 line? The public API shouldn&apos;t have changed. The devapidocs may have, but for the most part folks who need the earlier version should know how to get it (e.g. maven javadoc jars, the release, etc)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What about for 0.98 where more can change in each 0.98.y release?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14648354" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 30 Jul 2015 21:40:39 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;What do folks think about just publishing the most recent patch release in a given minor line, i.e. 1.1.1 for the 1.1 line?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;What about for 0.98 where more can change in each 0.98.y release?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we can still do the same for 0.98: publish docs for the most recent release. We already have documented elsewhere that expectations are different for 0.98. Will be less of an issue going forward as use of 0.98 tapers off toward EOL&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15332066" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 15 Jun 2016 16:44:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I find I&apos;m missing this as well. Can we bake publishing the latest release into the RC publication process or perhaps into the jenkins build for the release branches? I haven&apos;t looked into how it is we publish the master-SNAPSHOT API docs or how we have 0.94 API docs published separately.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15332067" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 15 Jun 2016 16:45:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To be clear, I&apos;d be happy with just versioning the API docs. We don&apos;t appear to have the dedicated interest to keep version-specific books up to date.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15332213" author="busbey" created="Wed, 15 Jun 2016 18:03:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the 0.94 docs live in the site repo and AFAICT never change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding in updating version specific docs into the &quot;publish &amp;amp; cleanup&quot; phase of closing out a release sounds like a good idea. It gives us a concrete timing and a person specifically tasked with taking care of it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m game as 1.2 RM if the other RMs don&apos;t have an objection. Or I guess if they do we can figure something out, since I&apos;ll still do it for 1.2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since I have the 1.2.2 vote open right now, we should figure out what this looks like before that release is ready to go. Anyone have time to work that out before Monday? If not I&apos;ll start planning my weekend &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15332214" author="busbey" created="Wed, 15 Jun 2016 18:04:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;and yes, please, just API docs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
